---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const pageTitle = 'Canyon Lake Neighborhoods | Cody Posey Real Estate';
const pageDescription = 'Explore Canyon Lake, TX neighborhoods — lakefront gated communities, Hill Country acreage, waterfront retreats, and family-friendly subdivisions near the water.';
const pageSchema = [
  articleSchema({ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, url: '/canyon-lake/neighborhoods' }),
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Canyon Lake', url: '/canyon-lake' },
    { name: 'Neighborhoods', url: '/canyon-lake/neighborhoods' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  schema={pageSchema}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="cl-hero">
      <div class="cl-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="cl-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/canyon-lake/">Canyon Lake</a> <span>/</span> <span>Neighborhoods</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Canyon Lake <span style="color:#FF1616;">Neighborhoods</span></h1>
        <p>Lakefront communities, gated estates, and Hill Country acreage</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="cl-page-intro cl-page-intro--centered">Canyon Lake is organized around a mix of lakefront and off-lake communities, each with a distinct character. Whether you want direct waterfront access, a gated neighborhood with resort-style amenities, or a quiet homesite on acreage with Hill Country views — there is an area here that fits.</p>
        <p style="max-width: 800px; margin: 1.5rem auto 0; color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.8; text-align: center;">The lake itself is a U.S. Army Corps of Engineers reservoir fed by the Guadalupe River, stretching over 8,200 acres with 80 miles of shoreline. The surrounding communities developed at different times and for different reasons — some were built for full-time residents who commute to San Antonio or New Braunfels, others cater to weekend retreaters and vacation homeowners. The result is a patchwork of communities that range from modest and affordable to high-end waterfront estates. Understanding the differences between these neighborhoods is essential for making the right buying decision. Every area has its own HOA rules, lake access situation, and price dynamics.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Neighborhoods -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Canyon Lake <span class="accent">Communities</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="cl-neighborhood__grid">
          <div class="cl-neighborhood__card">
            <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cl-canyon-lake-hills.png" alt="Canyon Lake Hills homes" class="cl-neighborhood__img" loading="lazy" />
            <h3>Canyon Lake Hills</h3>
            <p>An established, active community with waterfront on three sides, Canyon Lake Hills offers a peaceful, rural, lake-centric lifestyle. Amenities include a swimming pool, children's park, tennis courts, and a boat ramp. The neighborhood features a mix of full-time residents and vacation homes. Homes here range from older builds from the 1970s and 80s to fully renovated properties with modern finishes. Many lots back up to greenbelt areas, and the community boat ramp provides direct lake access without needing a private dock. Canyon Lake Hills has an active HOA that organizes seasonal events including Fourth of July celebrations and community cookouts.</p>
            <div class="cl-neighborhood__tags">
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">$300K - $800K</span>
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">Comal ISD</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cl-neighborhood__card">
            <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cl-mystic-shores.png" alt="Mystic Shores homes" class="cl-neighborhood__img" loading="lazy" />
            <h3>Mystic Shores</h3>
            <p>Nestled between the Guadalupe River and the north shore of Canyon Lake, Mystic Shores offers a tranquil, luxurious Hill Country lifestyle. Resort-like amenities include a community center, multiple pools, walking trails, sports courts, and parks. Properties range from 1 to 20+ acres with water or Hill Country views. The community is divided into distinct sections including The Shores, The Bluffs, and The Highlands, each with its own character and price tier. Architectural standards maintain a cohesive Hill Country aesthetic with stone and stucco exteriors. Mystic Shores attracts buyers who want acreage and privacy without sacrificing access to community amenities. The neighborhood is also popular with equestrian buyers, as many lots accommodate horse facilities.</p>
            <div class="cl-neighborhood__tags">
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">$350K - $700K</span>
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">Comal ISD</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cl-neighborhood__card">
            <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cl-oak-shores.png" alt="Oak Shores Estates homes" class="cl-neighborhood__img" loading="lazy" />
            <h3>Oak Shores Estates</h3>
            <p>An exclusive gated lakefront community on the south side of Canyon Lake, Oak Shores Estates features crystal-clear water views and custom homes on generous lots. Amenities include a homeowner's park with playscape and pool. The neighborhood is predominantly full-time residents. Homes in Oak Shores are typically custom-built with high-end finishes including stone facades, metal roofing, and expansive outdoor living areas designed to take advantage of lake views. Many properties include private boat docks with deep-water access. The gated entry and established tree canopy give the neighborhood a sense of seclusion that appeals to buyers looking for a premium, low-traffic lakefront setting.</p>
            <div class="cl-neighborhood__tags">
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">$500K - $4M+</span>
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">Comal ISD</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cl-neighborhood__card">
            <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cl-canyon-lake-estates.png" alt="Canyon Lake Estates homes" class="cl-neighborhood__img" loading="lazy" />
            <h3>Canyon Lake Estates</h3>
            <p>A well-established community around Canyon Lake, Canyon Lake Estates offers homeowner amenities including a pool and regular community events. The neighborhood features various home styles set among established landscaping, providing an accessible entry point to lake-area living. With homes starting in the mid $200K range, Canyon Lake Estates is one of the more affordable ways to live in the Canyon Lake area. The community includes a mix of single-story ranch homes and two-story builds from the 1990s through the 2010s. Lot sizes are modest compared to acreage communities, but the trade-off is lower maintenance and easy walkability within the neighborhood. This is a strong option for first-time buyers, retirees, and anyone who wants to be near the lake without paying lakefront prices.</p>
            <div class="cl-neighborhood__tags">
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">$250K - $500K</span>
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">Comal ISD</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cl-neighborhood__card">
            <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cl-hancock.png" alt="Hancock Area homes" class="cl-neighborhood__img" loading="lazy" />
            <h3>Hancock Area</h3>
            <p>Properties along Hancock Road in the historical Hancock Canyon area, which takes its name from the original Hancock community that was submerged when Canyon Lake was created in the 1960s. The area maintains a rural character with individual properties and land parcels. Hancock is ideal for buyers who want a no-frills, unrestricted country lifestyle near the lake. Many properties here sit on one to five acres with minimal deed restrictions, meaning more freedom for workshops, livestock, or accessory buildings. The area lacks the resort-style amenities of nearby communities but compensates with affordability and privacy. Hancock is also a popular area for investors looking at short-term vacation rental potential, given its proximity to the lake and the Guadalupe River.</p>
            <div class="cl-neighborhood__tags">
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">$200K - $400K</span>
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">Comal ISD</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cl-neighborhood__card">
            <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/cl-river-mountain-ranch.png" alt="River Mountain Ranch homes" class="cl-neighborhood__img" loading="lazy" />
            <h3>River Mountain Ranch</h3>
            <p>A luxurious acreage community along the Guadalupe River, River Mountain Ranch offers serene country living on spacious private lots. Residents enjoy two gated river parks with hiking, grilling, and river access for kayaking, tubing, and fishing. The community is horse-friendly, making it ideal for buyers seeking both space and a riverfront lifestyle. Lots typically range from 1 to 5+ acres, and homes feature Hill Country architectural styles with native stone, standing-seam metal roofs, and generous covered porches. The community enforces architectural guidelines to maintain its upscale, cohesive appearance. River Mountain Ranch appeals to families, equestrian enthusiasts, and professionals who commute to New Braunfels or San Antonio but prefer to come home to wide-open Hill Country landscapes and river access at the end of the day.</p>
            <div class="cl-neighborhood__tags">
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">$400K - $800K</span>
              <span class="cl-neighborhood__tag">Comal ISD</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- School District -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>School <span class="accent">District</span></h2>
          <p>Canyon Lake is served by one of the top-rated districts in the region</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cl-schools__grid">
          <a href="https://www.comalisd.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cl-schools__card">
            <h3>Comal ISD</h3>
            <p>One of the fastest-growing and highest-rated districts in Texas. Comal ISD serves the entire Canyon Lake area with multiple elementary, middle, and high school campuses.</p>
            <span class="cl-schools__link">Visit Comal ISD Website →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Need Help <span class="accent">Narrowing It Down</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">I can walk you through the differences between Canyon Lake communities and help you focus your search on neighborhoods that match your priorities.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Get Help Choosing a Neighborhood</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/canyon-lake-water.png" />

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Canyon Lake Neighborhoods</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What are the best Canyon Lake neighborhoods for families?</summary>
          <p>Canyon Lake Hills and Canyon Lake Estates are both strong choices for families. Canyon Lake Hills offers a community pool, children's park, and tennis courts with a welcoming mix of full-time residents. Canyon Lake Estates provides an affordable entry point to lake-area living with regular community events that help families connect. Both communities are served by Comal ISD, one of the highest-rated school districts in the region.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How much does it cost to live in a lakefront community at Canyon Lake?</summary>
          <p>Lakefront living at Canyon Lake varies widely depending on the community and whether the property has direct water access. Entry-level homes in Canyon Lake Estates start around $250K, while waterfront properties in Oak Shores Estates can exceed $4 million. For buyers who want to be near the lake without paying premium waterfront prices, communities like Canyon Lake Hills and Canyon Lake Estates offer lake-area living in the $250K to $500K range with shared community lake access through boat ramps and parks.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Are there Canyon Lake neighborhoods without HOA restrictions?</summary>
          <p>Yes. The Hancock area along Hancock Road is known for minimal deed restrictions, giving property owners more freedom with how they use their land. This makes it a popular choice for buyers who want to build workshops, keep livestock, or simply avoid the rules and fees that come with HOA-managed communities. Properties in Hancock typically sit on one to five acres and start in the low $200K range. For buyers who prefer a managed community with architectural standards, neighborhoods like Mystic Shores and River Mountain Ranch maintain active HOAs with established guidelines.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best Canyon Lake neighborhoods for families?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Canyon Lake Hills and Canyon Lake Estates are both strong choices for families. Canyon Lake Hills offers a community pool, children's park, and tennis courts with a welcoming mix of full-time residents. Canyon Lake Estates provides an affordable entry point to lake-area living with regular community events that help families connect. Both communities are served by Comal ISD, one of the highest-rated school districts in the region."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does it cost to live in a lakefront community at Canyon Lake?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Lakefront living at Canyon Lake varies widely depending on the community and whether the property has direct water access. Entry-level homes in Canyon Lake Estates start around $250K, while waterfront properties in Oak Shores Estates can exceed $4 million. For buyers who want to be near the lake without paying premium waterfront prices, communities like Canyon Lake Hills and Canyon Lake Estates offer lake-area living in the $250K to $500K range with shared community lake access through boat ramps and parks."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are there Canyon Lake neighborhoods without HOA restrictions?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. The Hancock area along Hancock Road is known for minimal deed restrictions, giving property owners more freedom with how they use their land. This makes it a popular choice for buyers who want to build workshops, keep livestock, or simply avoid the rules and fees that come with HOA-managed communities. Properties in Hancock typically sit on one to five acres and start in the low $200K range. For buyers who prefer a managed community with architectural standards, neighborhoods like Mystic Shores and River Mountain Ranch maintain active HOAs with established guidelines."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <ContactForm context="I'd like to learn more about Canyon Lake neighborhoods..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .cl-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/canyon-lake-water.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .cl-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .cl-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .cl-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cl-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .cl-page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .cl-page-intro--centered {
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Neighborhood Cards */
  .cl-neighborhood__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cl-neighborhood__card {
    background: #fff;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .cl-neighborhood__img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .cl-neighborhood__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    padding-right: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cl-neighborhood__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    flex: 1;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    padding-right: 2rem;
  }

  .cl-neighborhood__tags {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    padding-right: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .cl-neighborhood__tag {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--light-gray);
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  /* Schools */
  .cl-schools__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .cl-schools__card {
    display: block;
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cl-schools__card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .cl-schools__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: #000;
  }

  .cl-schools__card:hover h3 {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .cl-schools__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cl-schools__link {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cl-neighborhood__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
